The whole plain by now was filled with men and horses,\uc0\u8232 all in gleaming bronze. The ground shook underfoot,\u8232 as men charged each other. Two of the finest men\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0190\u8232 then came at one another in the middle ground\u8232 between the armies, both prepared for combat\'97\u8232 Aeneas, Anchises\'92 son, and godlike Achilles.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[160]\u8232 Aeneas strode out first, making threatening taunts,\u8232 his heavy helmet nodding as he moved around.\u8232 Holding his strong shield across his chest, he brandished\u8232 his bronze spear. The son of Peleus, from the other side,\u8232 charged up against him like a murderous lion\u8232 which a whole community is keen to slaughter\'97\u8232 At first, the beast moves on and leaves the group alone,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0200\u8232 but when some quick young hunter hits it with a spear,\u8232 the lion gathers itself, opens its jaws wide,\u8232 foaming at the mouth, as its brave heart roars inside.\u8232 Its tail twitches to and fro against its ribs and flanks.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[170]\u8232 Then it drives itself to fight, charging straight ahead\u8232 with furiously glaring eyes to kill someone\u8232 or die there in the first attack. That\'92s how Achilles,\u8232 driven by his furious proud heart, came on then\u8232 against the brave Aeneas. As they approached each other,\u8232 coming to close quarters, swift-footed Achilles yelled:\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\