2 into the ground. But it ripped apart two layers\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[280]\u8232 on that protective shield. Having escaped the spear,\u8232 Aeneas straightened up, eyes glazed with shock,\u8232 frightened that the spear had come so close to him.\u8232 Drawing his sword, Achilles launched a frenzied charge\u8232 with a blood-curdling scream. Aeneas picked up a rock,\u8232 a heavy lift, which no two men now alive could do,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0340\u8232 although he managed it with ease all by himself.\u8232 With that rock Aeneas would have struck Achilles,\u8232 as he charged at him, on his helmet or the shield\u8232 which had rescued him from death, and then Achilles\u8232 in close combat with his sword would have taken\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[290]\u8232 Aeneas\'92 life, had not the Earthshaker Poseidon\u8232 been paying attention. He spoke up immediately,\u8232 addressing the immortal gods beside him.\
